message:
RegExp() called with a `{
    includeSuffix = false,
    includePrefix = false,
    excludeOptionalTrailingSlash = false,
  }: GetRouteRegexOptions = {}` function argument, this might allow an attacker to cause a Regular Expression Denial-of-Service (ReDoS) within your application as RegExP blocks the main thread. For this reason, it is recommended to use hardcoded regexes instead. If your regex is run on user-controlled input, consider performing input validation or use a regex checking/sanitization library such as https://www.npmjs.com/package/recheck to verify that the regex does not appear vulnerable to ReDoS.
